Class AbstractSubscriptionTerm

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractDto
      • org.phoenixbioinformatics.api.db.api.AbstractSubscriptionTerm
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto, com.poesys.db.dto.IObserver, com.poesys.db.dto.ISubject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto>, ISubscriptionTerm
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SubscriptionTerm

    public abstract class AbstractSubscriptionTerm
extends com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractDto
implements ISubscriptionTerm

    A data-access layer data-transfer object for the SubscriptionTerm. This class is an abstract class that contains AndroMDA generated code; change nothing in this class. Instead, override any methods in the concrete subclass generated in the same package. AndroMDA will overwrite this class each time you run it but will never overwrite the concrete subclass.

    A standardized period of time and price for access during that period

    Stereotypes:

    • CompositeKey
    • Persistent

    Class is read/write: true

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
